            },
            {
                "name": "Bacteria",
                "url": "/topics/bacteria"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547883",
        "quote": "When antibiotics became industrially produced following World War II, our quality of life and our longevity improved enormously. No one thought bacteria were going to become resistant.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Bonnie Bassler",
            "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547883"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Thought",
                "url": "/topics/thought"
            },
            {
                "name": "Bacteria",
                "url": "/topics/bacteria"
            },
            {
                "name": "Became",
                "url": "/topics/became"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547885",
        "quote": "The goal of scientists is you hope that the thing you're working on is bigger than the thing you're pipetting into that tube at that moment.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Bonnie Bassler",
            "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547885"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Goal",
                "url": "/topics/goal"
            },
            {
                "name": "Tube",
                "url": "/topics/tube"
            },
            {
                "name": "Scientists",
                "url": "/topics/scientists"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547887",
        "quote": "All these bacteria that coat our skin and live in our intestines, they fend off bad bacteria. They protect us. And you can't even digest your food without the bacteria that are in your gut. They have enzymes and proteins that allow you to metabolize foods you eat.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Bonnie Bassler",
            "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547887"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Bad",
                "url": "/topics/bad"
            },
            {
                "name": "Bacteria",
                "url": "/topics/bacteria"
            },
            {
                "name": "Allow",
                "url": "/topics/allow"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547888",
        "quote": "Most bacteria aren't bad. We breathe and eat and ingest gobs of bacteria every single moment of our lives. Our food is covered in bacteria. And you're breathing in bacteria all the time, and you mostly don't get sick.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Bonnie Bassler",
            "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547888"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Bad",
                "url": "/topics/bad"
            },
            {
                "name": "Bacteria",
                "url": "/topics/bacteria"
            },
            {
                "name": "Mostly",
                "url": "/topics/mostly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547889",
        "quote": "In my lab, we are always thinking about how cells, bacterial cells, can talk to each other and then organize themselves into enormous groups that function in unison.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Bonnie Bassler",
            "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547889"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            },
            {
                "name": "Unison",
                "url": "/topics/unison"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547892",
        "quote": "Science is difficult and slow no matter who you are. The hours are long, and the glorious 'aha' days come only very infrequently. You have to keep believing that if you put in the hours, those days will indeed come!",
        "author": {
            "name": "Bonnie Bassler",
            "url": "/quotes/bonnie_bassler_547892"
